==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} ''[[payle]]'' "wooden container" from {{etyl|ang}} ''[[pægel|pæġel]]'' "wine vessel, container for liquids, pail; liquid measure". Akin to {{etyl|dum|-}} ''[[pegel#Middle Dutch|pegel]]'' "half pint", {{etyl|gml|-}} ''[[pegel#Middle Low German|pegel]]'' "half pint", {{etyl|dan|-}} ''[[pægel#Danish|pægel]]'' "half a pint" 

